4/6
http://www.socceramerica.com/article/12467/mls-summaries-april-6-four-games-finish-2-1.html

The scores were all the same in four MLS games on April 6:After celebrating their 2001 title win with a pregame ring ceremony, the San Jose Earthquakes won their home opener, 2-1, against New England in front of a disappointing crowd (announced as 10,104). San Jose improved to 2-1-0. New England, now 0-2-0 and in the midst of a four-game road trip, is hoping to avoid a repeat of last yearGs 0-7 start. ... Project-40 rookie Brad Davis proved the hero for the MetroStars, who downed the Crew in Columbus, 2-1, on his golden goal. ... Also decided on a golden goal: Los Angeles, 2-1, over Chicago. Carlos Ruiz's second goal of the evening came two minutes into overtime. The Guatemalan newcomer has scored twice in both 2002 games for the Galaxy (2-0-0). ... Dallas notched its first win of the year, downing D.C. United, 2-1, at the Cotton Bowl on goals by Jason Kreis and Jorge Rodriguez.April 6 in San JoseSan Jose 2 New England 1. Goals: Lagos (Graziani, Conrad) 2, Ekelund (Donovan, DeRosario) 78; Diallo (Ralston, Heaps) 38.SAN JOSE -- Cannon, Agoos, Conrad, Barrett, Dayak, Ekelund, Lagos (Corrales, 85), Russell, Mulrooney, Donovan, Graziani (DeRosario, 72)CAUTIONS: none; EJECTIONS: noneNEW ENGLAND -- Sommer, Cullen, Llamosa, Pierce, Joe Franchino, Ralston, Rooney, Heaps (Harris, 82), Chronopoulos (Twellman, 60), Chacon, DialloCAUTIONS: Chronopoulos 42, Pierce 53, Franchino 79; EJECTIONS: noneReferee: Kevin Terry.Att.: 10,104.April 6 in ColumbusColumbus 1 MetroStars 2 (OT)Goals: Washington (Perez, Harkes) 58; Faria (Villegas, Kamler) 69; Davis 97.COLUMBUS -- Presthus, Clark (Harkes, 23), Dunseth, Torres, Denton, Oughton, Maisonneuve, Perez, West (Yeagley, 83), Cunningham, DWashington (Buddle, 91)CAUTIONS: Oughton 25, Dunseth 70; EJECTIONS: Torres 73METROSTARS -- Howard, Kamler, Petke, Addo (Forko, 75), Jolley, Hernandez, Paule (Davis, 81), Mathis, Villegas (Ramos, 81), Faria, Serna.CAUTIONS: Addo 11, Howard 59, Davis 82, Hernandez 89; EJECTIONS: noneReferee: Ricardo Valenzuela.Attendance: 11,103.April 6 in Pasadena, Calif.Los Angeles 2 Chicago 1. Goals: Ruiz 81, Ruiz (Marshall, Hendrickson) 92; Razov (unassisted) 89.LOS ANGELES -- Reis, Hendrickson, Califf, Lalas, Frye, Cobi Jones, Cienfuegos (Mullan, 82), Elliott, Victorine (Marshall, 91), Albright (Glinton, 74), Ruiz.CAUTIONS: Hendrickson 17, Lalas 50, Ruiz 55; EJECTIONS: none.CHICAGO -- Thornton, Brown (Sleeth, 68), Gray,Beasley, Kovalenko, Armas, Nowak, Daniv (Moore, 82), Marsch, Wolff, Razov.CAUTIONS: Armas 38, Kovalenko 46, Moore 84; EJECTIONS: none.Referee: Ali Saheli.Attendance: 13,887.April 6 in DallasDallas 2 D.C. United 1. Goals: Kreis (Rhine, Broome) 63, Rodriguez (Pareja, Vaca) 84; Quaranta (Curtis, McKinley) 61.DALLAS -- Jordan, Suarez, Morrow, Bonseu, RichardFarrer, Broome, Rodriguez, Pareja, Martinez (Vaca, 46), Rhine (Johnson, 82), Kreis (Cerritos, 73)CAUTIONS: Farrer 2, Broome 74, Pareja 91+; EJECTIONS: none.D.C. UNITED -- Rimando, Reyes, Prideaux, Pope, McKinley, Etcheverry, Alavanja (Lisi, 87), Williams, Convey, Quaranta, Conteh (Curtis, 59).CAUTIONS: McKinley 13, Prideaux 21, Reyes 68, Alavanja 85, Etcheverry 86, Reyes 88, Williams 88; EJECTIONS: Reyes 88.Referee: Ricardo Salazar.Att.:: 8,565.


